divs: sighting detailsdriving on i-65 headed west i saw a green\yellow light shoot across the sky. at first i thought it was an extremely bright falling star but it was as bright as the moon and had a green shade to it. what really caught my attention was how it cut through the clouds and the only reason i believed it was that low, was because the light reflected on the clouds as it went through it. the reflection lit up that portion of the sky and then the light dissappeard as if it had been a falling star. i was driving southwest and the object was slighly to the left of me (south direction) and it was a little less then 45 degees above the horizon.
